{"id": "EUVD-2025-31952", "enisaUuid": "e21df8d8-4c3a-3cf1-b928-2671957bd8ab", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nvdpa: Add features attr to vdpa_nl_policy for nlattr length check\n\nThe vdpa_nl_policy structure is used to validate the nlattr when parsing\nthe incoming nlmsg. It will ensure the attribute being described produces\na valid nlattr pointer in info->attrs before entering into each handler\nin vdpa_nl_ops.\n\nThat is to say, the missing part in vdpa_nl_policy may lead to illegal\nnlattr after parsing, which could lead to OOB read just like CVE-2023-3773.\n\nThis patch adds the missing nla_policy for vdpa features attr to avoid\nsuch bugs.", "datePublished": "2025-10-07T15:19:48", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-07T15:19:48", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53652", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/44b508cc96889e61799cc0fc6c00766a54f3ab5a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/645d17e06c502e71b880b2b854930e5a64014640", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/79c8651587504ba263d2fd67fd4406240fb21f69"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53652", "GHSA-j5px-w2f8-7x3g"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0f71c40a-ebb2-3ec1-b12b-d3a3fa41eed5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.5"}, {"id": "26e534c2-c35d-3b64-817e-4d6ae93aaafa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.4.12"}, {"id": "2a02f961-c74b-3801-9d6b-7b77151ccaeb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.1"}, {"id": "6aef848c-8ccc-371e-9ead-59ccb8ba6b4e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "90fea5a800c3dd80fb8ad9a02929bcef5fde42b8 <645d17e06c502e71b880b2b854930e5a64014640"}, {"id": "7996d04f-7be5-324d-98b0-65f699175bdd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "90fea5a800c3dd80fb8ad9a02929bcef5fde42b8 <44b508cc96889e61799cc0fc6c00766a54f3ab5a"}, {"id": "91e98ec6-0a7c-36fe-979c-a8e15bd68ec6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version"